# Colibri Camera/Gimbal Driver — Implementation Plan

## Context

The `feature/ColibriCommandandControl` branch added a scaffold for a NextVision NightHawk-family camera/gimbal driver (the "Colibri" serial protocol) but the scaffold is incomplete and won't compile or work correctly:

- `app/include/ms_colibri_command_interface.h` defines the wire structs (good) but the encode/decode functions have wrong byte ordering, packed correlator bytes twice, use uninitialised checksum variables, and put `index += 8` where `+= 1` is meant. A free-floating `double k = …` lives in the header (ODR violation across translation units).
- `app/include/ms_vehicleData.h` declares `addNighthawkObserver(messageName, observer)` but `.cc` defines `addNighthawkObserver(observer)` — link error.
- `app/src/ms_vehicleData.cc` calls `nighthawk_interface.inputMessage(...)`; the method is `input_message`.
- `app/src/ms_gimbalControl.cc` has a stray `vehicleData->` token in `rotation_test()` — won't compile.
- `app/CMakeLists.txt` doesn't list `ms_colibri_command_interface.cc`, so the file is invisible to the build.
- The class is missing the observer-dispatch / output-observer API that the rest of the codebase uses (see `mavlink_interface` and `stanag_interface`).

The intended outcome: a working wire-level driver that correctly encodes outgoing Host→Camera (H2CAM) 20-byte command messages, decodes incoming Camera→Host (CAM2H) 20-byte and 64-byte Full-ACK reports per *Colibri Protocol Rev 2.0.43* (May 2025), dispatches decoded reports to observers using the same pattern as `mavlink_interface`, and exposes a small high-level command API on `ms_gimbalControl`. The camera and gimbal share one physical serial link and one protocol, so a single driver covers both.

Protocol default: **Full ACK (fast) mode** — 115,200 bps, 100 Hz reports, 64-byte CAM2H. Header3 = `0xF8` (auto-roll, yaw-stabilise) is issued on the first command to flip the camera link out of slow mode. The HDMI-sync developer guide explicitly states fast mode is the only mode intended for high-accuracy systems.

## Approach

Restructure `ms_colibri_command_interface` to mirror `mavlink_interface` (the established pattern in this repo): a non-`kw_component` class that lives as a member of `ms_vehicleData`, owns named-observer dispatch, has overloaded `send_message(struct)` methods, and an `addOutputObserver(kw_observer*)` that funnels encoded bytes out through `mOUTPUT_GIMBAL`. `ms_gimbalControl` becomes the consumer — it registers as an observer for decoded acks, holds the latest gimbal state, and exposes a handful of typed setters (mode, rate, FOV, channel, LRF) that build a `__colibri_message_command` and call into the interface.

