### 2. `app/src/ms_colibri_command_interface.cc` — full implementation

Implement:

- `static uint8_t colibri_checksum(const uint8_t* buf, int len)` — 8-bit additive sum of `buf[0..len-2]` (standard for this family; flag in a `// TODO` comment that this needs HW verification on first integration).
- `bool colibri_command_encode(const __colibri_message_command& m, uint8_t out[20])` — pack the 20 bytes in the correct order per *Colibri Protocol Rev 43* §3.1 (page 9-13). Use one `out[idx++] = m.field;` per byte. The struct is already `#pragma pack(push,1)` and lays out the fields in protocol order, so a `memcpy(out, &m, 19)` works for the body; then `out[19] = colibri_checksum(out, 20)`.
- `bool colibri_fixed_ack_decode(__colibri_message_ack& m, const uint8_t in[20])` — `memcpy` body + validate checksum; return false on mismatch.
- `bool colibri_full_ack_decode(__colibri_message_full_ack& m, const uint8_t in[64])` — same.
- `input_message(uint8_t* data, int len)` — append bytes to `rx_buffer`, scan for header `0xB0 0x3B`, then peek the expected message length (20 for slow / known headers `0x77..0x7A` and `0x83`; 64 for fast / `0xF7..0xFA` echo). On a valid checksum, decode into the cached struct, then `notify(mCOLIBRI_ACK_FIXED|FULL, &cached_*)`. Discard the consumed bytes; if header sync is lost, shift one byte and keep scanning.
- `send_message(const __colibri_message_command& m)` — encode, wrap in `stBuffer`, forward to `outputObserver->update(mCOLIBRI_MESSAGE_ENCODED, &buf)`.
- `notify`, `addObserver`, `addOutputObserver` — copy verbatim from `mavlink_interface.cc` (same shape).
- `get_gimbal_az/el/fov` — convert the cached MSB/LSB pairs to degrees using the 14-bit formula in *Camera Optical Report v1.5* §3.1 and the FOV formula `100 / 1.03^report` from *Colibri Rev 43* §4.2 correlator 0x04.

Reuse: `pack/unpack` from `pack_unpack.h` is available but unnecessary for this protocol — all fields are byte-aligned uint8_t. Stick with direct byte assignment for clarity.

