### 7. `app/src/ms_gimbalControl.cc` — implement

- Constructor seeds `cmd_template.header1=0xB0; header2=0x3B; header3=0xF8;` (fast-mode auto-roll/yaw-stab).
- `createComponent` registers `this` with `vehicleData->addNighthawkObserver(mCOLIBRI_ACK_FULL, this)` and `mCOLIBRI_ACK_FIXED`.
- Each setter mutates the appropriate bits of `cmd_template`, then calls `send_current_command()` which does `vehicleData->nighthawk_interface.send_message(cmd_template)`. The 5-bit Mode lives in bits `[0..4]` of byte 3; channel/illuminator/fusion in bits `[7..5]` of byte 3.
- `setRate` encodes the 12-bit signed pitch/roll/yaw values into bytes 14-18 per *Rev 43* §3.1 byte 14-18 layout, with the centre value 2048 added (see Appendix A §1.i).
- `setFOV` builds a correlator-0x05 command: byte 9 bits [5..0] = `0x05`, bytes 10-11 = MSB/LSB of deg×10, bytes 12-13 = 0x00.
- `fireLRF` sets byte 4 bit 4 (and the appropriate safety key in byte 6 bits[7..4]=`0x5`).
- `processUpdate` casts `data` to `__colibri_message_full_ack*` for `mCOLIBRI_ACK_FULL` (or fixed ack) and caches relevant state for getters / downstream consumers.
- Empty out the previous `mainThread` body to just `while (running) std::this_thread::sleep_for(std::chrono::seconds(1));` (no polling needed — commands are caller-driven; acks arrive via observer).

